15:53:04 [INFO]   Recovered JSON from error on data:text/plain,CALL FOR APPLICATIONS – SEPTEMBER 2026 INTAKE
The MSc in Economics is a full-time graduate program run jointly by the Department of Economics and the Department of
International & European Economic Studies, of the School of Economic Sciences, at the Athens University of Economics and
Business (AUEB). Its aim is to educate and train economists of high scientific standards in the fields of Economic Theory and
Policy. Its graduates are expected to continue their studies at a PhD level, and/or to work at international organizations,
central banks, research institutes, national ministries, private banks and big companies, etc.
We welcome applications from graduates from various scientific fields like Economics, International and European
Economic Studies, Regional Economics, Finance, Statistics, Mathematics, Physics, Engineering, Informatics.
The tuition fees are 2500€. The Program consists of 3 semesters. The language of instruction and exams is English.
Applications are submitted exclusively online at https://e-graduate.applications.aueb.gr/?lang=en_US, until 30/6/2026.
Submission process:
1. Connect to the above link.
2. Register and log in.
3. Find the “M.Sc. in Economics (Full Time)” among the programs listed in the School of Economic Sciences list.
4. Complete all required fields in the application form (including photo)
5. Upload all required documents (as stated below in this call).
Notice: The process is completed by clicking the “Submit” button.
If any personal data is not applicable (e.g. the “social security number”), please type “-“.
Available admissions are limited. Evaluation of the applicants and admission offers are made throughout the application
period and in order of priority.
More information on the Program’s Website: https://www.dept.aueb.gr/en/gradecon
For queries contact the Program’s Secretariat at post.econ@aueb.gr or tel. 0030 210 8203617, 0030 210 8203644 (Monday-
Friday 11:00-13:00)
REQUIRED DOCUMENTS:
1. University Degree with official transcript or Certificate of completion of studies with official transcript (if not in
English or Greek, a certified copy of English translation is also required).
2. Certificate of strong command of the English language (Level C1 or C2) (e.g. TOEFL with a grade greater than 79,
IELTS with a grade greater than 7, TOEIC with a grade greater than 785, etc). Applicants who don’t own the
certificate when applying, must submit a solemn declaration of article 8 of Greek Law 1599/1986 declaring that, in
case they are accepted to the Program, they must submit the certificate in due course.
3. Two academic recommendation letters. They must be sent directly by the referees (academic staff) to the
Program’s Secretariat electronically (either by email or uploaded to the online applications portal).
The above documents are initially submitted only online. A certified hard copy of the English language certificate maybe
asked to be submitted at a later stage.
Submission of an application to this call does not imply admission.
The Athens University of Economics and Business is committed to ensuring equal opportunities and rights in work and
education.
Athens, 18/2/2026
The Director of the MSc in Economics Program The Rector
* *
Professor Elias Tzavalis Professor Vasilios Vasdekis
